p.01703376c4a81c0e9d91: Adds a regex filter clause onto a query
p.01703376c4a81c0e9d92:
Adds a `regex` predicate to the given query. This predicate indicates to the query to filter out the objects whose the specified property does not match the provided regular expression.

The OR operator ( | ) is not supported
The query to which the regex filter must be added
The property used by the filter to execute the predicate to check if that property matches the given regular expression.

The value to which the property is compared. Check if the property matches that regular expression. It has to be a valid regex, depending on what is supported by your database and data connector used.
If true, take care of the case, otherwise apply the regular expression on the property value changed to lower case.
